The story he gave me included the part where he intentionally aggrevated Kempo in /ooc.  <br>
<br>
The officers know his main's name and none of us will reveal it to anyone who asks, especially someone who has threatened him.  <br>
<br>
I will freely admit to not listening very long to Kempo's explanation.  It was sounding like a highly edited version of the story I had.<br>
And after I got tired of listening to excuses, I stopped answering his tells afterwards.<br>
<br>
When giving any explanation for a /guildremoval, I try to make it as brief and with as few details as possible for the former member's benefit.<br>
&quot;Conduct unbecoming a member of Blood Circle&quot;...<br>
&quot;Scamming&quot;...<br>
&quot;Training&quot;...<br>
or whatever seems appropriate at the time.<br>
<br>
I hate guildremoving people and it's the most miserable duty I have as the Guildleader.  I will not ask any other officer to do it in my place.<br>
I have only been forced to removed 3 people from the guild in my time as an officer.<br>
<br>
I said it in guildchat that evening and I will say it again here.  <br>
If any of you have concerns about the fairness of my actions in this, feel free to send me a tell and I will sit down and talk to you any time.<br>
